<subSubSection id="841946557C3676336FA266B96F5901D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="8330F760847C10B971EC5B600AE74547" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40767C3F0774555EA100E30D63BD9272" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
Asexual morph: Colonies are compact, round, dark to black, 80-320 in diameter. Mycelium is composed of hyaline to pale brown smooth hyphae 2-7 
<normalizedToken id="C289529C24B5C68842FA9CB4B00123AA" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter. Conidiophore mother cells spherical to lageniform, hyaline with brown pigments at the base, measuring (4
<normalizedToken id="F092CDD5F3DC609F97E787AB16A5E3D6" originalValue="–)5–7(–">-)5-7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="11F2F4D4532077BFE21B93B01A44B330" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(4
<normalizedToken id="ED026CB5BD1AC931A6FA6CDEB347375B" originalValue="–)5–6(–">-)5-6(-</normalizedToken>
7) 
<normalizedToken id="3E7463F9CC18C536D3D395D6B9276A35" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30). Conidiophores cylindrical unbranched, straight or flexuous, hyaline and smooth walled, with a single brown transversal septa, measuring 30-100 
<normalizedToken id="A55A3CD929634BC3E79EEAAA279E0679" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 
<normalizedToken id="44AEF465930B4A2A30204EE061313ADB" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. (n = 30). Conidiogenous cells cylindrical 1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="32B09CBDF4806CC62FD790A0C0578647" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="5A54F73AC6A8B638EADC18D931D1C79E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(n = 20). Conidia borne along the sides of conidiophores, curved, rounded at the ends, brown, with a hyaline germ slit and a clearly visible scar, (8
<normalizedToken id="C99AFABA1C61FA0762E8260FCD12653F" originalValue="–)9–10(–">-)9-10(-</normalizedToken>
11) 
<normalizedToken id="FCB85374EF02050E5D9AE1851D040EA2" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long in frontal view, (5
<normalizedToken id="DCF914F0DC5EFA4DD977A89099AE66CB" originalValue="–)6–7(–">-)6-7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="77A1BB5133BAB66DD88858F3815229DE" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in side view (n = 30). Sterile cells rounded, paler than conidia. Culture characteristics flat colonies spreading on MEA 2% with moderate aerial mycelium, reverse withish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2804032F7BC1D9BACD9C0C648399D0A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F4AA00D71816ECED5E58DB3F0E6C8AEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="059D48564030403EDBC4D63DA260ABBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="C43C83866F2B3F3BFB1246FE8BB6E2C5" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium curvatum var. minus" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="minus">Arthrinium curvatum var. minus</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="643C100C7F4265C3A95A4B060EFE1968" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="A. curvatum var. curvatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="curvatum">A. curvatum var. curvatum</taxonomicName>
, but conidia of var. 
<taxonomicName id="287A2103FCEACCBA1E94F007B03C56AE" lsidName="var. minus" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" variety="minus">minus</taxonomicName>
measure (8
<normalizedToken id="ACE2B1EB0897476A26BD95F2CF4090E7" originalValue="–)9–10(–">-)9-10(-</normalizedToken>
11) 
<normalizedToken id="D0F2EC0DC4C6E5B9C0E3B214C8777190" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(5
<normalizedToken id="EC268503B6E0B3D32932D2A03B20FED3" originalValue="–)6–7(–">-)6-7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="872B9C4459FFC944366921C4CDDC4F95" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, while those of 
<taxonomicName id="02BFCB8DE807B841A7721E2935C99C0C" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="A. curvatum var. curvatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="curvatum">A. curvatum var. curvatum</taxonomicName>
measure 11-15 
<normalizedToken id="26DD8EFA663AABF31E1289119AFA0451" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 
<normalizedToken id="2529F3A9DF6403EE11CB0C8A58AD2898" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Gutner (1927) described 
<taxonomicName id="E16F1B8B2F589DE6E21697B9729E1361" authority="Gutner" authorityName="Gutner" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hyponectriaceae" genus="Pseudoguignardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pseudoguignardia scirpi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="scirpi">Pseudoguignardia scirpi</taxonomicName>
, a sexual morph of 
<taxonomicName id="B33FF7AE5C5AB359FE4CCB6F46205CA5" genus="A." lsidName="A. curvatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="curvatum">A. curvatum</taxonomicName>
, later combined as 
<taxonomicName id="48754128D06B598DEAD1F034695743E5" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hyponectriaceae" genus="Physalospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Physalospora scirpi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="scirpi">Physalospora scirpi</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18F32348BC21EA02A81A5C54FF146864" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Arx 1970</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="9C9D216F298872F9100BAB3953FC36B3" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium curvatum var. minus" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="minus">Arthrinium curvatum var. minus</taxonomicName>
is closely related with 
<taxonomicName id="DF7040B8A8006BD0029D3A72771B4DED" genus="A." lsidName="A. sporophleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="sporophleum">A. sporophleum</taxonomicName>
(with lemon-shaped conidia) and 
<taxonomicName id="CA5AF1AF360741DB81EDB998FA3C9C66" genus="A." lsidName="A. japonicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="japonicum">A. japonicum</taxonomicName>
(with larger fusiform conidia) and to a lesser extent also with 
<taxonomicName id="5BEDCA21B8E993B22873730B7387F5FD" genus="A." lsidName="A. caricicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="caricicola">A. caricicola</taxonomicName>
(with larger fusiform conidia) and 
<taxonomicName id="B3DA4CFDB05F72F76CABB593E4E64FE5" genus="A." lsidName="A. puccinioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="puccinioides">A. puccinioides</taxonomicName>
(with polygonal conidia). 
<bibRefCitation id="5AA6B319627EDC9BF82C6BA731B052D0" author="Ellis, MB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="497 - 514" title="British marsh and fen fungi. II." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(51)80034-2" volume="34" year="1951">Ellis et al. (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="50D0B60A6CB9CBC452EA1B053BF6B20C" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="A. curvatum var. minus" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="minus">A. curvatum var. minus</taxonomicName>
, a taxon with similarly shaped but smaller conidia than 
<taxonomicName id="24A8D62BC7C3E8DFC5D94153E367B53D" genus="A." lsidName="A. curvatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="curvatum">A. curvatum</taxonomicName>
. The specimen studied in the present work matches the shape and size of conidia reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="27CB1C01CBF1D000D81EDA3A70A6AFE6" author="Ellis, MB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="497 - 514" title="British marsh and fen fungi. II." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(51)80034-2" volume="34" year="1951">Ellis et al. (1951)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="481E405464FE30516A8FF50497F817A3" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="A. curvatum var. minus" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="minus">A. curvatum var. minus</taxonomicName>
, rather than those of 
<taxonomicName id="858A078812F8466BC5F610D5A8BEF152" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="A. curvatum var. curvatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" species="curvatum" variety="curvatum">A. curvatum var. curvatum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4533494393B5AACEE65E86EA0F4C55F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="materials_examined">
